## 🗄 Database Schema
```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS products (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    sku TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    brand_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK(brand_type IN ('batya', 'buy', 'volna')),
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT DEFAULT '',
    price_ozon INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    price_direct INTEGER DEFAULT NULL,
    ozon_url TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
    image_local_path TEXT DEFAULT '',
    is_active INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
    sort_order INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
CREATE INDEX idx_products_brand ON products(brand_type);
CREATE INDEX idx_products_active ON products(is_active);
CREATE INDEX idx_products_sku ON products(sku);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS submissions (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    phone TEXT NOT NULL,
    email TEXT DEFAULT '',
    product_id INTEGER DEFAULT NULL,
    message TEXT DEFAULT '',
    source TEXT DEFAULT 'website',
    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (product_id) REFERENCES products(id)
);

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS sync_log (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    started_at DATETIME NOT NULL,
    finished_at DATETIME DEFAULT NULL,
    status TEXT DEFAULT 'running',
    products_updated INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    errors TEXT DEFAULT '',
    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
🎨 Design & UI
Theme: Industrial Dark Mode
Color palette:
Background primary: #0a0a0f
Background secondary: #12121a
Background tertiary: #1a1a2e
Surface: #1e1e2e
Border: #2a2a3e
Text primary: #e8e8f0
Text secondary: #a0a0b8
Text muted: #6b6b80
Accent (orange): #f97316
Accent hover: #ea580c
Brand colors:
BATYA: #d97706 (amber)
BUY: #2563eb (blue)
VOLNA: #059669 (emerald)
Fonts:
Primary: Inter (sans-serif) — all UI text
Mono: JetBrains Mono — prices, numbers, technical data
Responsiveness: mobile-first, breakpoints sm(640px), md(768px), lg(1024px), xl(1280px)
JavaScript:
Brand filtering without page reload (fetch + DOM update)
Modals: pure JS with native <dialog> element
Forms submitted via fetch() with JSON server response handling
Smooth scrolling for anchor navigation
Icons: inline SVG or emoji (🔧 БАТЯ, 🚗 БУЙ, 🎣 ВОЛНА)
📦 Coding Standards
Always declare(strict_types=1); at the top of every PHP file
Naming:
Classes: StudlyCaps
Methods: camelCase
Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
Variables: camelCase
DB columns: snake_case
PSR-12 formatting (enforce with php-cs-fixer)
Type declarations: use for ALL properties, parameters, return types
SQL: ONLY PDO prepared statements with named params; NEVER string concatenation
Error handling: try/catch inside services, log to file, re-throw to controller level
Logging format: [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS] [LEVEL] Message (INFO, WARNING, ERROR)
Paths: absolute paths via __DIR__ and constants from config.php
Security:
CSRF tokens on ALL forms (generate + validate)
Server-side input validation and sanitization
htmlspecialchars() for ALL output
.htaccess protection for sensitive directories (core/, config/, database/, logs/)
🔌 Ozon Seller API Integration
Base URL: https://api-seller.ozon.ru
Auth headers:
Client-Id: {OZON_CLIENT_ID}
Api-Key: {OZON_API_KEY}
Primary endpoint: POST /v3/product/info/list
Request body: {"offer_id": ["SKU1", "SKU2", ...]}
Sync strategy:
SKU list stored in config/config.php
Cron runs daily at 03:00 MSK
Admin can trigger manual sync via admin/sync.php
On sync: update price, title, description, image, is_active
If product missing from API → set is_active = 0
API keys: placeholders until real keys provided
OZON_CLIENT_ID = 'your_client_id_here'
OZON_API_KEY = 'your_api_key_here'
📱 Telegram Integration
API URL: https://api.telegram.org/bot{TOKEN}/sendMessage
Parameters: chat_id, text, parse_mode: HTML
Message format:
text

🆕 Новая заявка с сайта uzelok64.ru

👤 Имя: {name}
📞 Телефон: {phone}
📧 Email: {email}
📦 Товар: {product_title}
💬 Комментарий: {message}

🕐 {datetime}
Placeholders:
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = 'your_bot_token_here'
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = 'your_chat_id_here'
🚀 Deployment & CI/CD
GitHub Actions (.github/workflows/deploy.yml):
Trigger: push to main
Steps: checkout → PHP lint → php-cs-fixer (dry-run) → SFTP upload to Beget
Exclude: .git, node_modules, .env, database/*.db, logs/*
Pre-deploy checklist:
config/config.php exists on server (not overwritten)
database/ and logs/ have write permissions (chmod 755)
PHP 8.4 active on Beget; SQLite extension enabled
.htaccess: rewrite to index.php, deny access to sensitive dirs, gzip, HTTPS redirect, security headers
🧪 Local Development
Dev server: php -S localhost:8000 -t public_html
Without Ozon API keys: OzonService returns mock data from config/mock-products.json
Tailwind CDN for dev; compiled for production
DB auto-creates on first run if file missing
🤖 AI-Specific Instructions (Cursor)
Strictly follow all rules in this file when generating code
Never suggest Laravel, Symfony, Slim, Yii, jQuery, React, Vue, Angular
Always use PDO prepared statements with named parameters for ALL SQL
Before creating a new class, check if existing class in core/ can be reused
Forms: always include CSRF token generation and validation
Logs: English messages, ISO 8601 timestamp, severity level
Comments: explain complex logic only; no obvious comments
File placement: EXACTLY in directories described in Project Structure
PHP 8.4 features: use enums, readonly, constructor promotion, match, named args
Templates: plain PHP with <?= htmlspecialchars($var) ?> for output
Config: NEVER hardcode credentials; read from config or env
Images: product images → public_html/assets/images/products/{sku}.jpg
🔄 Updating Rules
Update this file when requirements change
AI must read this file before starting any task
